      • getLogEntries

        public java.util.List<LogEntry> getLogEntries(int first,
                                              int last)
        Description copied from interface: Log
        Returns the log entries of this transaction in specified range. They are ordered from old to new.

        Must hold true: 0 <= first <= last

        Specified by:
        getLogEntries in interface Log
        Parameters:
        first - the first entry to be received.
        last - the last entry to be received.
        Returns:
        returns all log entries of this transformation beginning with the given first index up to the given last index of all entries. If no entries are available in given range, returns an empty List. The Produced list is not mutable!

      • getLogEntries

        public java.util.List<LogEntry> getLogEntries(int firstIndex)
        Description copied from interface: Log
        Like Log.getLogEntries(int first, int last), but omits the lastIndex. Therefore, beginning with start index, all following log entries are returned.
        Specified by:

        Returns:
